==English==
===Etymology===
*From [[rho]], the Greek letter ''r''

===Adjective===
'''rhotic'''

#Of an English accent, pronouncing the letter ''r'' wherever it appears in a word, as in ''bar'' ([[w:IPA|IPA]] /bɑːr/) and ''bard'' or ''barred'' (IPA /bɑːrd/); this trait is common most of the United States, many parts of the north of England, Scotland, and India.

